<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM2.4.10">
<l>kārmali mēṉi niṟattuk kaṇṇa pirāṉai yukantu</l>
<l>vārmali koṅkai yacōtai mañcaṉa māṭṭiya vāṟṟaip</l>
<l>pārmali tolputu vaikkōṉ paṭṭar pirāṉcoṉṉa pāṭal</l>
<l>cīrmali centamiḻ vallār tīviṉai yātu milarē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master the refined Tamil, full of excellence,</l>
<l>of [this] song, composed by Paṭṭarpirāṉ, king of ancient Putuvai,</l>
<l>that spreads across the earth,</l>
<l>about how Yaśodā, with plentiful, girdled breasts,</l>
<l rend="indent">having desired [to give a bath to] Lord Kṛṣṇa</l>
<l rend="indent">with a bodily complexion abounding in darkness,</l>
<l rend="indent">made [him] take a ceremonial bath,</l>
<l>for them, there will be no bad karma.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
